matchHeader.status: Kolkata Knight Riders won by 106 runs

status: Kolkata Knight Riders won by 106 runs

videos.headline: Russell to Nortje, out Caught by Shreyas Iyer!! That's the game! This is a massive, massive victory for KKR!! Ian Bishop on air mentions that it's the first time in the history of IPL that KKR have won their first three matches of the season on the trot. A back of a length delivery, Nortje backs away and mistimes his flat-batted stroke to mid-on and holes out to Shreyas Iyer. Beaming smiles in the KKR camp. This has been a proper drubbing. Nortje c Shreyas Iyer b Russell 4(6)

Vaibhav Arora to Rasikh Salam, out Caught by Philip Salt!! The short ball pays dividends to Vaibhav Arora once again! He has looked impressive tonight. He bowls a well-directed bouncer which gets big on Rasikh Salam. He is rushed on the pull and top-edges it to Philip Salt's right. The keeper takes it with ease. Rasikh Salam c Philip Salt b Vaibhav Arora 1(5)

Narine to Sumit Kumar, out Caught by (sub)Manish Pandey!! Wickets falling in clusters now! Tossed up delivery on a length, Sumit Kumar looks to heave it over deep mid-wicket but doesn't get proper elevation and power behind the shot. Manish Pandey, the substitute, is safe as houses. Sumit Kumar c (sub)Manish Pandey b Narine 7(6) [6s-1]

Chakaravarthy to Tristan Stubbs, out Caught by Starc!! Tristan Stubbs falls against the run of play! Chakaravarthy looks up the heavens and thanks his stars. Was a length ball drifting down leg, Tristan Stubbs mistimed his expansive stroke towards deep backward square leg. Starc took a few steps in and didn't make any mistake. Tristan Stubbs c Starc b Chakaravarthy 54(32) [4s-4 6s-4]

Chakaravarthy to Axar, out Caught by (sub)Manish Pandey at straight down the ground!! Two wickets in two balls for Chakaravarthy! Brilliant take from Manish Pandey. Tossed up delivery around off, Axar goes for a big hit straightaway and toe-ends it towards long-on. Manish Pandey, the substitute fielder, runs in. There's another fielder in his vicinity running in from mid-wicket but he stays calm. Gets low, takes the catch with both hand, and then falls down on the ground. Axar c (sub)Manish Pandey b Chakaravarthy 0(1)

Chakaravarthy to Pant, out Caught by Shreyas Iyer!! Pant's entertaining knock comes to an end! Chakaravarthy bowls this one on a fuller length wide outside off. Pant has to reach out to it. Perhaps not the right shot selection to go for the slog sweep but he goes for it. Ends up skewing it off the outer half of the bat over covers. Shreyas Iyer calls for it and takes a smart catch. Pant c Shreyas Iyer b Chakaravarthy 55(25) [4s-4 6s-5]

Starc to Warner, out Bowled!! Chopped on. Starc gets his countryman. Shortens the length, slows the pace and keeps it outside off. Warner wanted to stab it on the off-side but instead got a thick inside edge that deflected to smash the middle of middle peg. 4 down are the Delhi Capitals and their dug-out pose a sorry look as Warner trudges back to the pavilion. Warner b Starc 18(13) [4s-2 6s-1]

Vaibhav Arora to Abishek Porel, out Caught by Narine!! No impact from DC's impact sub unfortunately. He gets an excellent short ball from Vaibhav Arora - had nowhere to hide - and gets hurried on the pull. Flies high off the top-edge and Narine accepts the dolly at short fine. DC are in huge trouble now. Abishek Porel c Narine b Vaibhav Arora 0(5)

Vaibhav Arora to Abishek Porel, out Caught by Narine!! No impact from DC's impact sub unfortunately. He gets an excellent short ball from Vaibhav Arora - had nowhere to hide - and gets hurried on the pull. Flies high off the top-edge and Narine accepts the dolly at short fine. DC are in huge trouble now. Abishek Porel c Narine b Vaibhav Arora 0(5)

Starc to Mitchell Marsh, out Caught by Ramandeep Singh !! Mitchell gets Mitchell. It's the 1st wicket for Starc in IPL 2024. Bowls it full and wide of off, Marsh senses an opportunity to free his arms and goes hard on the drive. End result? Slices it straight into the hands of Ramandeep Singh at backward point. Mitchell Marsh c Ramandeep Singh b Starc 0(2)

Vaibhav Arora to Prithvi Shaw, out Caught by Chakaravarthy!! Another in-ducker from Vaibhav Arora and Prithvi Shaw's attempted heave finds the thick inside edge. It flies low to the left of mid-on where Varun Chakaravarthy dives full length to grab an excellent catch inches above the turf. Managed to get his fingers under the ball and was in firm control of the catch as well. Knew he got it clean straightaway and started celebrating instantly. Prithvi Shaw c Chakaravarthy b Vaibhav Arora 10(7) [4s-2]

Ishant to Ramandeep Singh, out Caught by Prithvi Shaw!! Ishant drags the length back and keeps it well wide of off, Ramandeep Singh chases and looks to smash it over sweeper cover. Skews it off the thick inside half and Prithvi runs across to his left from cover to take a fine catch. Remember, KKR are just 2 sixes away from achieveing something phenomenal here. Ramandeep Singh c Prithvi Shaw b Ishant 2(2)

Ishant to Russell, out Bowled!! Build a statue to this man - Ishant Sharma - the supporters of SRH must be screaming right now. Mustafizur, when playing for SRH, did something simialr to Russell in 2016 IPL and now Ishant Sharma repeats the dose. A toe-crushing yorker that makes Russell fall onto the floor quite awkwardly. By the time he could bring his bat down, the stumps were in an amazing state of mess. The leg peg has gone north and the middle peg goes the opposite direction. Russell b Ishant 41(19) [4s-4 6s-3]

Nortje to Rinku Singh, out Caught by Warner!! A low full toss once again and this time Rinku Singh fails to get the desired connection. Loses shape trying to heave into the off-side and skews it off the toe-end towards mid-on. Warner leaps up to his fullest and claims the catch with an air of calmness. Rinku Singh c Warner b Nortje 26(8) [4s-1 6s-3]

Khaleel Ahmed to Shreyas Iyer, out Caught by Mitchell Marsh!! It's the short ball once again! Shreyas Iyer looked to heave it from wide of off and didn't really get hold off the pull. Flew off the toe end high into the night sky and Stubbs settles under it at mid-off. Shreyas Iyer c Mitchell Marsh b Khaleel Ahmed 18(11) [6s-2]

Nortje to Angkrish Raghuvanshi, out Caught by Ishant at third man!! End of a terrific knock on batting debut from Angkrish Raghuvanshi. Nortje bowled it short and wide of off, Raghuvanshi thought he could ramp it for a six and opened the bat face really late. Khaleel was placed at fine third man and he didn't need to move an inch. Straight down his throat and a much-needed wicket this for DC. Angkrish Raghuvanshi c Ishant b Nortje 54(27) [4s-5 6s-3]

Mitchell Marsh to Narine, out Caught by Pant!! That's the end of the Narine show tonight, he walks off to a big round of applause though - excellent bowling from Marsh, banged this one short, went cross-seam and made Narine swat against the line, the edge is found and Pant holds on. That'll relieve them of some serious pressure, but Narine has done a superb job once again. Narine c Pant b Mitchell Marsh 85(39) [4s-7 6s-7]

Nortje to Philip Salt, out Caught by Tristan Stubbs!! Warner can heave a sigh of relief, that missed chance hasn't cost a lot - pitched up by Nortje and Salt is once again cramped up for space, was looking to play the lofted drive, the bat turned on impact and skewed high towards mid-off - Stubbs backpedalled, kept watching the ball and reverse cupped it with ease, even as he fell on his back. Philip Salt c Tristan Stubbs b Nortje 18(12) [4s-4]
